### Macro Knobs (New Feature)
- *Dependency: ControlConnection/ControlPort*
- MacroControl is a panel with a basic graph node that contains outbound control ports.
- Any component with controllable parameters gets an inbound Macro assignment slot, and a corresponding indicator on the parameter control widget indicating it is controlled.
- Internally, it has a basic formula editor to convert the generic knob value towards whatever parameters it is connected to.
- It also is capable of receiving modulation input.
- The MacroKnob is also capable of receiving control input from MIDI (but probably not another MacroKnob)":TY

### MIDI Control Mapping (New Feature)
- *Dependency: ControlConnection/ControlPort*
- Component to turn midi signal into control signal
- Only allow one control signal per parameter, so that MidiControl and MacroKnob don't compete
- UI gives touch-learn midi assignment (either wiggle control or tap button to assign. Potentially filter based on parameter type and control type )
- [Quick] Indicator on parameter showing MIDI association, hover to reveal control id

### Peripheral Devices
- [Big] Support Audio Input peripherals
- [Big] Allow multiple MIDI peripheral devices
- [Big] Support MIDI output peripherals

### Components to Add
- [Quick] Bitcrusher
- [Quick] AudioSwitch (send audio through output channel 0 or 1)
- [Quick] MidiSwitch (leverage midi channel system)
- [Medium] Quantizer / velocity manipulation
- [Big] Arpeggiator
- [Big] Mixer *note: investigate whether this should be a primary component or a configured GroupComponent (e.g., chained panners with some scalar controls or something)*
  
